cs.MA, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT

The paper deals with optimization-based approaches to model cooperation and competition between multiple ridesharing companies, which involves the use of algorithms and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the use of Mobility as a Service (MaaS) platforms, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also presents model variants coping with noise in the travel time estimations and bias in the assignment costs, which are related to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses worst-case bounds and preferences in the competitive case, which are related to the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
